      "text": "Here\u0027s the translation of the provided text, aiming for maximum accuracy. Please let me know if you have any questions about specific terms.\n\n## Laws of the Maldives\n\n**Law on Condominium Buildings**\n\n**Chapter One: Preliminary**\n\n**Introduction and Name**\n\n**1.**\n(a) This is a law to register buildings in the Maldives as condominium buildings, to specify the principles for the acquisition, sale, and ownership of units within condominium buildings, to outline the principles for the management and use of condominium buildings.\n(b) This law shall be called the \"Law on Condominium Buildings\".\n\n**Objectives**\n\n**2.** The objectives of this law are as follows:\n(a) To establish the principles related to the registration of buildings constructed in the Maldives as condominium buildings;\n(b) To facilitate the acquisition of units within condominium buildings by individuals or parties, to determine the methods of unit ownership, and to facilitate the process of residing in, buying, selling, renting, and conducting other transactions within the parts of condominium buildings;\n(c) To determine the principles for the management and use of the land and common areas of buildings registered as condominium buildings, and to define the rights and responsibilities of the owners of individual units within the building and land;\n(d) To provide opportunities for developers to expand real estate businesses in the Maldives, and to establish a system for conducting transactions related to condominium buildings and for managing condominium buildings based on sound principles and standards.\n\n**Chapter Two: Definitions**\n\n**Basis of Definitions**\n\n**3.**\n(a) The terms and phrases defined in this Chapter are the fundamental concepts upon which this Law is based.\n(b) The definitions provided in this Law are intended to preserve the original intent of this Law and to facilitate the achievement of its objectives to the fullest extent. Accordingly, every article of this Law shall be interpreted in a manner that does not limit those definitions.\n\n**Share Unit**\n\n**4.** \"Share Unit\" refers to the share allocated to a unit or units included in the Schedule of Strata Units prepared in conjunction with the strata plan.\n\n**Original Owner of the Land**\n\n**5.** \"Original Owner of the Land\" refers to the party or parties stated in the land registry prior to or at the time of applying for the registration of a condominium building as the owner of the land.\n\n**Management**\n\n**6.** \"Management\" refers to the maintenance and upkeep of a condominium building, and the management of common areas and facilities within the condominium building by the Management Corporation in accordance with the principles and standards determined by it, for the benefit and interest of the unit owners.\n\n**Condominium Building**\n\n**7.** \"Condominium Building\" refers to a building constructed or to be constructed as follows:\n(a) Comprising one or more stories, comprising units and common areas clearly defined as separate parts, forming a single organizational structure without attachment to other buildings;\n(b) Divided into units with separately owned parts, and with common areas in which all unit owners have equal shares.\n\n**Common Areas**\n\n**8.** \"Common Areas\" refers to areas outside the boundaries of individual units included in the strata plan. However, if a duct or ventilation shaft within the boundaries of a unit connects to another unit, that area shall be considered a common area. Common areas are areas in which all unit owners have equal shares. These include the following:\n(a) Common Areas (Common areas include areas designated as common areas in the strata plan, as well as walkways, corridors, stairs, elevator shafts, and ventilation shafts within the building.)\n(b) Common Facilities (Common facilities include facilities within or connected to common areas that are shared by the unit owners of the condominium building, as determined in the strata plan.)\n\n**Land of the Condominium Building**\n\n**9.** For the purposes of this Law, \"Land of the Condominium Building\" refers to the land designated as the plot for the condominium building.\n\n**Building**\n\n**10.** For the purposes of this Law, \"Building\" refers to buildings that meet the following criteria:\n(a) The building comprises or is planned to comprise one or more stories, including units and common areas;\n(b) The building or buildings are constructed or planned to be constructed in a manner that allows for the separate ownership of units within them, with common areas in which all unit owners have equal shares.\n\n**Accessory Unit**\n\n**11.** \"Accessory Unit\" refers to any space within the condominium building, including parking space for a vehicle, that is allocated for additional uses by the owner of a unit in the condominium building, in conjunction with that unit, as designated in the condominium building\u0027s plan.\n\n**Boundary**\n\n**12.** \"Boundary\" refers to the fence that separates the following:\n(a) The boundary defining the part of a unit belonging to the owner of that unit;\n(b) The boundary separating one unit from another;\n(c) The boundary separating units from common areas.\n\n**Developer**\n\n**13.** \"Developer\" refers to the party developing a condominium building in the Maldives in accordance with the applicable laws and regulations at the time.\n\n**Defect Liability Period**\n\n**14.** \"Defect Liability Period\" refers to the period stipulated in the construction agreement, commencing from the date of completion of the building, within which the developer is obligated to rectify or repair any defects in the building at their own expense.\n\n**Initial Period**\n\n**15.** In a stage development, the \"Initial Period\" refers to the period from the date of issuance of the strata plan approval until the sale of at least one-third (1/3) of the total share units included in the strata plan. This initial period concludes upon the first general meeting of the Management Corporation.\n\n**Management Corporation**\n\n**16.** \"Management Corporation\" refers to a corporation established among the owners of all units in a condominium building for the purpose of managing and maintaining the common areas and common facilities of the condominium building, in accordance with Article 95 of this Law.\n\n**Maintenance Fund**\n\n**17.** \"Maintenance Fund\" refers to a fund established by the owners of units in a condominium building or buildings to cover the recurring expenses associated with the use and maintenance of the building.\n\n**Limited Common Property**\n\n**18.** \"Limited Common Property\" refers to common areas designated for specific units within a condominium building. These areas shall be managed and maintained by the owners of the designated units under the supervision of the Management Corporation.\n\n**Purchaser**\n\n**19.** \"Purchaser\" refers to any party, including individuals and legal entities, intending to purchase a unit in a condominium building.\n\n**Strata Scheme**\n\n**20.** \"Strata Scheme\" refers to the principles established for the use and management of common areas between all unit owners, for a building or buildings constructed or to be constructed on land in accordance with the strata scheme, following the approval of the strata plan.\n\n**Strata Plan**\n\n**21.** \"Strata Plan\" refers to the plan prepared for the division of land and buildings constructed or to be constructed into units in accordance with the strata scheme, indicating the division of the building or buildings into separate parts, the share allocated to each unit, and the areas designated as common areas.\n\n**Schedule of Strata Units**\n\n**22.** \"Schedule of Strata Units\" refers to the table detailing the units included in the strata plan, their respective details, dimensions, and the share allocated to each unit in relation to its strata plan.\n\n**Sinking Fund**\n\n**23.** \"Sinking Fund\" refers to a fund established by the owners of units in a condominium building or buildings to cover the capital expenses associated with the use and maintenance of the building.\n\n**Strata Scheme**\n\n**24.** \"Strata Scheme\" refers to the scheme formulated in accordance with specific principles and standards under this Law, upon the approval of the strata plan for a building or buildings constructed or planned to be constructed comprising units and common areas.\n\n**Stage Development**\n\n**25.** \"Stage Development\" refers to the process of developing a building or strata scheme on a piece of land by submitting a proposal for the building, preparing a strata plan, and executing the project or strata scheme in phases.\n\n**Strata Roll**\n\n**26.** \"Strata Roll\" refers to the records maintained by the Management Corporation containing information about the units in a condominium building, the owners of those units, and information related to mortgages and insurance concerning the condominium building and its units.\n\n**Unit Registry**\n\n**27.** \"Unit Registry\" refers to the registry issued in the name of the owner of a unit within a condominium building under this Law.\n\n**Unit Owner**\n\n**28.** \"Unit Owner\" refers to the party stated in the unit registry as the owner of a unit included in the strata plan.\n\n**Unit**\n\n**29.** \"Unit\" refers to a separately ownable part within a building or buildings constructed or planned to be constructed under a strata plan. Such a unit may be a single story or multiple stories, forming a distinct entity. The strata plan must specify whether such a unit is a flat/apartment for residential use or a unit for commercial use.\n\n**Chapter Three: Determination of Parts of Land and Buildings**\n\n**Determination of Parts of Land and Buildings**\n\n**30.** In accordance with the principles set forth in this Chapter, the parts of the land and building comprising each strata plan shall be determined.\n\n**Conditions to be Met by Buildings**\n\n**31.** To obtain approval for a strata plan, the building or buildings must meet the following conditions:\n(a) The building or part thereof, comprising units and common areas on one or more floors, must be constructed as a distinct entity without attachment to other buildings, under a single organizational structure;\n(b) Basic services must be provided in the land and building, and in the individual units within the land and building;\n(c) There must be arrangements for separate access to and from each unit without hindering the use of other units or causing inconvenience;\n(d) The land and building for which strata plan approval is sought must conform to the standards stipulated in the Law on Construction, the Land Act, construction regulations, and planning regulations, and must have been approved by the relevant government authority.\n\n**Designated Use of Parts of Land and Buildings**\n\n**32.** The parts of buildings and land constructed or planned to be constructed under this Law shall be designated for the following uses:\n(a) Solely for residential purposes;\n(b) Solely for commercial purposes;\n(c) For both residential and commercial purposes.\n\n**Chapter Four: Approval of Strata Plans**\n\n**Obtaining Approval for Strata Plans**\n\n**33.**\n(a) A strata plan shall be prepared and submitted for approval to the Ministry by the original owner of the land or their designated representative, in accordance with the principles set forth in this Chapter.\n(b) Applications for strata plan approval shall be submitted to the Ministry using the form designated by the Ministry.\n\n**Buildings Eligible for Strata Plan Approval**\n\n**34.**\n(a) Applications for strata plan approval may be submitted for completed buildings, buildings where parts or units are completed, or buildings planned for new development or stage development.\n(b) For the purposes of subsection (a) of this Article, a completed building is one for which a building use permit has been issued. A building where parts or units are completed is considered to be a building where at least 2 (two) units are constructed on one or more floors.\n\n**Procedures for Obtaining Strata Plan Approval**\n\n**35.**\n(a) The details of the drawings of the land and building to which the strata plan relates, the format of such drawings, and the preparation of the schedule of strata units and share schedule related to the land and building to which the strata plan pertains shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n(b) To ensure that the land to which the strata plan relates is suitable for residential use, the minimum standards for such land shall be determined in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Information Required in Strata Plans**\n\n**36.** The strata plan submitted for approval must include the following information:\n(a) Whether the land to which the strata plan relates is private or government land;\n(b) The land or building registration number;\n(c) The name of the registered land, or the name of the project if it is a building planned for development under a stage development;\n(d) Details of the units and common areas comprising the land and building;\n(e) The extent of the share of each unit, and the total share extent of all units;\n(f) Dimensions of the parts specified in subsection (c) of this Article;\n(g) Other information specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Documents Required for Strata Plan Approval**\n\n**37.** When applying for strata plan approval, the following documents must be submitted along with the strata plan:\n(a) The application form for strata plan approval;\n(b) A document confirming the approval of the strata plan;\n(c) A copy of the completion certificate or a report signed by the project manager or engineer indicating the completion of the building;\n(d) Other information specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Application for Strata Plan Approval Under Stage Development**\n\n**38.** When applying for strata plan approval under a stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The application form for strata plan approval under stage development;\n(b) A document confirming the approval of the strata plan;\n(c) A progress report signed by the project manager or engineer, confirming that the project is proceeding in accordance with the stages outlined in the stage development agreement concluded between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(d) The latest amended Schedule of Strata Units;\n(e) The building use permit issued for the completed part of the building;\n(f) Other information required by the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans for Completed Buildings**\n\n**39.** Strata plan approval for completed buildings shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That all common areas of the building comprising the approved strata plan are completed and have been surveyed, and that the building conforms to the submitted strata plan;\n(b) That basic services are provided in the building, and that a building use permit has been issued for the building for which the strata plan approval is sought for at least 2 (two) units which are completed and have basic services provided.\n\n**Obtaining Approval for Strata Plans of Buildings with Completed Parts**\n\n**40.** When applying for strata plan approval for buildings where parts or units are completed, in addition to the documents specified in Article 52 of this Law, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The permit issued for the use of the completed part of the building;\n(b) Other information specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans for Buildings with Completed Parts**\n\n**41.** Strata plan approval for buildings with completed parts or units shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That all common areas related to the units for which the strata plan approval is sought are completed and have been surveyed, and that the building conforms to the submitted strata plan;\n(b) That at least 2 (two) units of the building are completed, basic services are provided for those 2 (two) units, and a building use permit has been issued for the part of the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Obtaining Approval for Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**42.** When applying for strata plan approval under a stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The application form for strata plan approval under stage development;\n(b) A document confirming the approval of the strata plan;\n(c) A progress report signed by the project manager or engineer, in accordance with the stages of the project outlined in the agreement concluded between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(d) The latest amended Schedule of Strata Units;\n(e) The building use permit issued for the completed part of the building.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**43.** Strata plan approval under stage development shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That the proposal submitted for carrying out the stage development project has been approved, and that an agreement for stage development has been signed between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(b) That all common areas related to the units for which strata plan approval is sought are completed, and that the building use permit has been issued for the parts of the building for which the strata plan approval is sought, conforming to the submitted strata plan;\n(c) That at least 20% (twenty percent) of the building for the stage development project has been completed, basic services are provided for those units, and a building use permit has been issued for the part of the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Amendment to Strata Plans**\n\n**44.** If an amendment is desired to a strata plan for which approval has been granted, the amendment can be made in accordance with the following procedures:\n(a) If any unit owner whose unit is affected by the proposed amendment to the strata plan has mortgaged their unit, the mortgagee must consent to the amendment;\n(b) If the amendment is passed by a general resolution of the Management Corporation;\n(c) If the resolution described in subsection (b) of this Article is passed with the votes of at least 80% (eighty percent) of the total share of all unit owners.\n\n**Documents Required for Strata Plan Amendments**\n\n**45.** When applying for amendments to a strata plan, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The application form for amending the strata plan;\n(b) A copy of the latest approved and amended drawings;\n(c) A copy of the permit issued for the strata plan under this Law;\n(d) The amended strata plan, the amended Schedule of Strata Units, and the share schedule in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law;\n(e) A copy of the building use permit, if issued;\n(f) The general resolution of the Management Corporation approving the amendment to the strata plan, affixed with the corporation\u0027s seal;\n(g) If the amendment to the strata plan is made during the initial period, the documents required to be submitted for amending in accordance with the regulations governing stage development under this Law.\n\n**Amendment to Share Units**\n\n**46.** The extent of the share allocated to units included in an approved strata plan may be amended in the following circumstances:\n(a) To amend the share unit allocated to a unit, to correct an error in the strata plan;\n(b) To amend the share unit due to a court order;\n(c) To make amendments to the building in accordance with the principles and standards for stage development provided in Chapter Seven of this Law;\n(d) To make amendments resulting from a redevelopment plan as specified in Article 47 of this Law.\n\n**Redevelopment of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**47.** If a condominium building is dilapidated or damaged due to an accident, or if the owners of the units in the condominium building wish to renovate the building, a redevelopment plan shall be prepared and submitted to the Ministry for approval in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Construction of Condominium Buildings by Consolidating Multiple Plots**\n\n**48.** If the original owner(s) of the land wish to develop a condominium building by consolidating multiple registered plots of land, application for development shall only be made after consolidating all the plots into a single registry. Furthermore, upon such consolidation, the share of each owner corresponding to their respective units must be recorded in the registry.\n\n**Application for Approval of Strata Plans for Stage Development**\n\n**49.** When applying for approval of strata plans under stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The proposal for the stage development project submitted for approval;\n(b) The agreement for stage development concluded between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(c) A progress report signed by the project manager or engineer, indicating that the project is proceeding in accordance with the stages outlined in the agreement for stage development.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**50.** Approval of strata plans under stage development shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That the proposal submitted for carrying out the stage development project has been approved, and that an agreement for stage development has been signed between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(b) That all common areas related to the units for which strata plan approval is sought are completed, and that the building use permit has been issued for the parts of the building for which the strata plan approval is sought, conforming to the submitted strata plan;\n(c) That at least 20% (twenty percent) of the building for the stage development project has been completed, basic services are provided for those units, and a building use permit has been issued for the part of the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Application for Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**51.** When applying for strata plan approval under stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The application form for strata plan approval under stage development;\n(b) A document confirming the approval of the strata plan;\n(c) A progress report signed by the project manager or engineer, confirming that the project is proceeding in accordance with the stages outlined in the stage development agreement concluded between the parties;\n(d) The latest amended Schedule of Strata Units;\n(e) The building use permit issued for the completed part of the building.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans for Completed Buildings**\n\n**52.** Approval of strata plans for completed buildings shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That all common areas of the building comprising the strata plan are completed and have been surveyed, and that the building conforms to the submitted strata plan;\n(b) That at least 2 (two) units of the building are completed, basic services are provided for those 2 (two) units, and a building use permit has been issued for the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Obtaining Approval for Strata Plans of Buildings with Completed Parts**\n\n**53.** When applying for strata plan approval for buildings where parts or units are completed, in addition to the documents specified in Article 52 of this Law, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The application form for amending the strata plan;\n(b) A copy of the latest approved and amended drawings;\n(c) A copy of the permit issued for the strata plan under this Law;\n(d) The amended strata plan, the amended Schedule of Strata Units, and the share schedule in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law;\n(e) A copy of the building use permit, if issued;\n(f) The general resolution of the Management Corporation approving the amendment to the strata plan, affixed with the corporation\u0027s seal;\n(g) If the amendment to the strata plan is made during the initial period, the documents required to be submitted for amending in accordance with the regulations governing stage development under this Law.\n\n**Amendment to Share Units**\n\n**54.** The extent of the share allocated to units included in an approved strata plan may be amended under the following circumstances:\n(a) To amend the share unit allocated to a unit, to correct an error in the strata plan;\n(b) To amend the share unit due to a court order;\n(c) To make amendments to the building in accordance with the principles and standards for stage development provided in Chapter Seven of this Law;\n(d) To make amendments resulting from a redevelopment plan as specified in Article 47 of this Law.\n\n**Procedure for Amending Strata Plans**\n\n**55.** If an amendment is desired to a strata plan for which approval has been granted, the amendment can be made in accordance with the following procedures:\n(a) If any unit owner whose unit is affected by the proposed amendment to the strata plan has mortgaged their unit, the mortgage must consent to the amendment;\n(b) If the amendment is passed by a general resolution of the Management Corporation, provided that the resolution is passed with the votes of at least 80% (eighty percent) of the total share of all unit owners.\n\n**Documents Required for Amending Strata Plans**\n\n**56.** When applying for amendments to a strata plan, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The application form for amending the strata plan;\n(b) A copy of the latest approved and amended drawings;\n(c) A copy of the permit issued for the strata plan under this Law;\n(d) The amended strata plan, the amended Schedule of Strata Units, and the share schedule in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law;\n(e) A copy of the building use permit, if issued;\n(f) The general resolution of the Management Corporation approving the amendment to the strata plan, affixed with the corporation\u0027s seal;\n(g) If the amendment to the strata plan is made during the initial period, the documents required to be submitted for amending in accordance with the regulations governing stage development under this Law.\n\n**Redevelopment of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**57.** If a condominium building, or buildings planned for development under a strata scheme, is dilapidated or damaged due to an accident, or if the owners of the units in the condominium building wish to renovate the building, a redevelopment plan shall be prepared and submitted to the Ministry for approval in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Consolidation of Multiple Plots for Construction of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**58.** If the original owner(s) of the land wish to develop a condominium building by consolidating multiple registered plots of land, application for development shall only be made after consolidating all the plots into a single registry. Furthermore, upon such consolidation, the share of each owner corresponding to their respective units must be recorded in the registry.\n\n**Application for Approval of Strata Plans for Stage Development**\n\n**59.** When applying for strata plan approval under stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The proposal for the stage development project submitted for approval;\n(b) The agreement for stage development concluded between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(c) A progress report signed by the project manager or engineer, confirming that the project is proceeding in accordance with the stages outlined in the stage development agreement.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**60.** Approval of strata plans under stage development shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That the proposal submitted for carrying out the stage development project has been approved, and that an agreement for stage development has been signed between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(b) That all common areas related to the units for which strata plan approval is sought are completed, and that the building use permit has been issued for the parts of the building for which the strata plan approval is sought, conforming to the submitted strata plan;\n(c) That at least 20% (twenty percent) of the building for the stage development project has been completed, basic services are provided for those units, and a building use permit has been issued for the part of the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Application for Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**61.** When applying for strata plan approval under stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The application form for strata plan approval under stage development;\n(b) A document confirming the approval of the strata plan;\n(c) A progress report signed by the project manager or engineer, confirming that the project is proceeding in accordance with the stages outlined in the stage development agreement concluded between the parties;\n(d) The latest amended Schedule of Strata Units;\n(e) The building use permit issued for the completed part of the building.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**62.** Approval of strata plans under stage development shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That the proposal submitted for carrying out the stage development project has been approved, and that an agreement for stage development has been signed between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(b) That all common areas related to the units for which strata plan approval is sought are completed, and that the building use permit has been issued for the parts of the building for which the strata plan approval is sought, conforming to the submitted strata plan;\n(c) That at least 20% (twenty percent) of the building for the stage development project has been completed, basic services are provided for those units, and a building use permit has been issued for the part of the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Amendment to Strata Plans**\n\n**63.** If an amendment is desired to a strata plan for which approval has been granted, the amendment can be made in accordance with the following procedures:\n(a) If any unit owner whose unit is affected by the proposed amendment to the strata plan has mortgaged their unit, the mortgage must consent to the amendment;\n(b) If the amendment is passed by a general resolution of the Management Corporation, provided that the resolution is passed with the votes of at least 80% (eighty percent) of the total share of all unit owners.\n\n**Circumstances for Amending Share Units**\n\n**64.** The extent of the share allocated to units included in an approved strata plan may be amended under the following circumstances:\n(a) To amend the share unit allocated to a unit, to correct an error in the strata plan;\n(b) To amend the share unit due to a court order;\n(c) To make amendments to the building in accordance with the principles and standards for stage development provided in Chapter Seven of this Law;\n(d) To make amendments resulting from a redevelopment plan as specified in Article 47 of this Law.\n\n**Procedure for Amending Strata Plans**\n\n**65.** If an amendment is desired to a strata plan for which approval has been granted, the amendment can be made in accordance with the following procedures:\n(a) The details of the proposed amendment to the strata plan must be submitted;\n(b) A copy of the latest approved and amended drawings;\n(c) A copy of the permit issued for the strata plan under this Law;\n(d) The amended strata plan, the amended Schedule of Strata Units, and the share schedule in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law;\n(e) A copy of the building use permit, if issued;\n(f) The general resolution of the Management Corporation approving the amendment to the strata plan, affixed with the corporation\u0027s seal;\n(g) If the amendment to the strata plan is made during the initial period, the documents required to be submitted for amending in accordance with the regulations governing stage development under this Law.\n\n**Amendment of Share Units**\n\n**66.** The extent of the share allocated to units included in an approved strata plan may be amended considering the following when amending the Schedule of Strata Units and the share extent allocated to units in accordance with Article 43 of this Law:\n(a) If a unit included in an approved strata plan has been sold, or if a registry has been issued for that unit, the share extent allocated to that unit may be amended only with the consent of the party who purchased the unit;\n(b) If a unit included in an approved strata plan under a stage development has not been sold, the share extent allocated to that unit may be amended without altering the total share extent of the building, after ensuring the latter.\n\n**Redevelopment of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**67.** If a condominium building is dilapidated or damaged due to an accident, or if the owners of the units in the condominium building wish to renovate the building, a redevelopment plan shall be prepared and submitted to the Ministry for approval in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Construction of Condominium Buildings by Consolidating Multiple Plots**\n\n**68.** If the original owner(s) of the land wish to develop a condominium building by consolidating multiple registered plots of land, application for development shall only be made after consolidating all the plots into a single registry. Furthermore, upon such consolidation, the share of each owner corresponding to their respective units must be recorded in the registry.\n\n**Information to be Included in the Unit Registry**\n\n**69.** The information to be included in the registry of each unit within a condominium building shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Condominium Building Registry**\n\n**70.**\n(a) Upon approval of the strata plan, a registry of the condominium building comprising all units shall be prepared and maintained by the Council of the relevant city or island. A copy of this registry, certified as true to the original, shall be provided by the Council to the Management Corporation of the condominium building.\n(b) If the ownership of any unit included in the registry of a condominium building changes after the registration of the condominium building, that change shall be reflected in the condominium building registry in accordance with this Law and the regulations made thereunder.\n(c) If the ownership of any unit included in the registry of a condominium building changes, or if any amendments are made to the registry, that information shall be shared with the Management Corporation within 14 (fourteen) days of such change or amendment, in accordance with this Law and the regulations made thereunder.\n(d) Upon the creation of the condominium building registry in accordance with this Article, the land registry or the building and land registry pertaining to that building shall become void.\n\n**Issuance of Unit Registry**\n\n**71.** Before issuing a unit registry for units within a condominium building, the following shall be ensured:\n(a) The authenticity of the documents submitted for registering the units;\n(b) That all fees payable to the government for the registration of units or for amendments to the unit registry under this Law and the regulations made thereunder have been paid;\n(c) If there are multiple owners for a unit within a condominium building, as described in subsection (b) of Article 85 of this Law, only one registry shall be issued for that unit;\n(d) That the requirements specified in the regulations made under this Law are met.\n\n**Registration of Units Under Stage Development**\n\n**78.** When applying for the registration of units within a condominium building under stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The form designated by the Ministry for applying for the registration of a unit within a condominium building under stage development;\n(b) Documentation from the original owner of the land for the sale of the unit within the condominium building;\n(c) A sales agreement or agreement registered with a court, notarized by a licensed notary public of the Maldives;\n(d) If the rental agreement is for the purchase of a unit, proof of full payment of the purchase price to the seller, or documentation of the payment plan;\n(e) If the land or unit of the condominium building is mortgaged, a document indicating the mortgagee\u0027s consent to the registration of the condominium building;\n(f) Other documents required to be submitted in accordance with the regulations made under this Law for stage development.\n\n**Registration of Completed Buildings\u0027 Strata Plans**\n\n**79.** When applying for strata plan approval for completed buildings, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The application form for strata plan approval;\n(b) A document confirming the approval of the strata plan;\n(c) A completion certificate or a report signed by the project manager or engineer indicating the completion of the building;\n(d) Other information specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans for Completed Buildings**\n\n**80.** Strata plan approval for completed buildings shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That all common areas of the building comprising the approved strata plan are completed and have been surveyed, and that the building conforms to the submitted strata plan;\n(b) That at least 2 (two) units of the building are completed, basic services are provided for those 2 (two) units, and a building use permit has been issued for the part of the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Obtaining Approval for Strata Plans of Buildings with Completed Parts**\n\n**81.** When applying for strata plan approval for buildings where parts or units are completed, in addition to the documents specified in Article 52 of this Law, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The permit issued for the use of the completed part of the building;\n(b) Other information specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**82.** Approval of strata plans under stage development shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That the proposal submitted for carrying out the stage development project has been approved, and that an agreement for stage development has been signed between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(b) That all common areas related to the units for which strata plan approval is sought are completed, and that the building use permit has been issued for the parts of the building for which the strata plan approval is sought, conforming to the submitted strata plan;\n(c) That at least 20% (twenty percent) of the building for the stage development project has been completed, basic services are provided for those units, and a building use permit has been issued for the part of the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Application for Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**83.** When applying for strata plan approval under stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The application form for strata plan approval under stage development;\n(b) A document confirming the approval of the strata plan;\n(c) A progress report signed by the project manager or engineer, confirming that the project is proceeding in accordance with the stages outlined in the stage development agreement concluded between the parties;\n(d) The latest amended Schedule of Strata Units;\n(e) The building use permit issued for the completed part of the building.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**84.** Approval of strata plans under stage development shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That the proposal submitted for carrying out the stage development project has been approved, and that an agreement for stage development has been signed between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(b) That all common areas related to the units for which strata plan approval is sought are completed, and that the building use permit has been issued for the parts of the building for which the strata plan approval is sought, conforming to the submitted strata plan;\n(c) That at least 20% (twenty percent) of the building for the stage development project has been completed, basic services are provided for those units, and a building use permit has been issued for the part of the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Amendment to Strata Plans**\n\n**85.** If an amendment is desired to a strata plan for which approval has been granted, the amendment can be made in accordance with the following procedures:\n(a) If any unit owner whose unit is affected by the proposed amendment to the strata plan has mortgaged their unit, the mortgage must consent to the amendment;\n(b) If the amendment is passed by a general resolution of the Management Corporation, provided that the resolution is passed with the votes of at least 80% (eighty percent) of the total share of all unit owners.\n\n**Circumstances for Amending Share Units**\n\n**86.** The extent of the share allocated to units included in an approved strata plan may be amended under the following circumstances:\n(a) To amend the share unit allocated to a unit, to correct an error in the strata plan;\n(b) To amend the share unit due to a court order;\n(c) To make amendments to the building in accordance with the principles and standards for stage development provided in Chapter Seven of this Law;\n(d) To make amendments resulting from a redevelopment plan as specified in Article 47 of this Law.\n\n**Redevelopment of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**87.** If a condominium building is dilapidated or damaged due to an accident, or if the owners of the units in the condominium building wish to renovate the building, a redevelopment plan shall be prepared and submitted to the Ministry for approval in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Consolidation of Multiple Plots for Construction of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**88.** If the original owner(s) of the land wish to develop a condominium building by consolidating multiple registered plots of land, application for development shall only be made after consolidating all the plots into a single registry. Furthermore, upon such consolidation, the share of each owner corresponding to their respective units must be recorded in the registry.\n\n**Ownership of Parts of Land and Buildings**\n\n**89.**\n(a) Unless otherwise specified in this Law, upon the registration of a condominium building, the owner of each unit in the building shall be considered the owner of the land in proportion to the share allocated to that unit in the strata plan and schedule of strata units.\n(b) The purchase, sale, gift, devise, or mortgage of units within a condominium building shall be restricted to Maldivian citizens, companies, partnerships, cooperative societies, or associations registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership.\n(c) Companies, partnerships, or cooperative societies registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership that have purchased units in a condominium building shall not sell any share of their ownership to foreign parties.\n(d) When selling a unit in a condominium building, the owner of the unit must ensure that the purchaser agrees to abide by the responsibilities and obligations of the Management Corporation and to comply with the decisions and regulations of the Management Corporation.\n(e) A unit in a condominium building may have more than one owner.\n(f) Notwithstanding subsection (e) of this Article, a unit in a condominium building shall not be subdivided or divided. Furthermore, in no event shall a unit in a condominium building be subdivided to allow more than one family to reside therein by separately connecting utilities such as electricity, water, or other services.\n\n**Transfer of Rights**\n\n**90.**\n(a) Unless otherwise specified in this Law or any other law, upon the sale, gift, devise, or mortgage of a unit in a condominium building by its owner, all rights and obligations of the owner of that unit under this Law shall transfer to the purchaser, donee, or legatee of that unit from that moment onwards.\n(b) If ownership of a unit in a condominium building changes due to sale, gift, devise, or mortgage, the registry of that unit shall be amended in the name of the new owner in accordance with this Law.\n(c) The ownership of common areas in a condominium building by the owner of a unit is a right shared equally with the owners of other units, and it is inseparable from that unit. Therefore, any transaction such as sale, gift, devise, or mortgage of common areas shall be conducted in a manner that does not prejudice the rights of other unit owners and in accordance with the strata scheme.\n(d) When a unit owner of a condominium building sells, gifts, devises, or mortgages their unit, the unit purchaser, donee, or legatee shall acquire ownership of the unit in proportion to their share of the common areas, in accordance with the strata plan.\n\n**Ownership of Land and Units in Buildings**\n\n**91.**\n(a) Unless otherwise specified in this Law, the owner of each unit in a condominium building constructed on government or private land shall be considered the owner of the land in proportion to the share allocated to that unit in the strata plan and schedule of strata units.\n(b) The purchase, sale, gift, devise, or mortgage of units within a condominium building shall be restricted to Maldivian citizens, companies, partnerships, cooperative societies, or associations registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership.\n(c) Companies, partnerships, or cooperative societies registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership that have purchased units in a condominium building shall not sell any share of their ownership to foreign parties.\n(d) When selling a unit in a condominium building, the owner of the unit must ensure that the purchaser agrees to abide by the responsibilities and obligations of the Management Corporation and to comply with the decisions and regulations of the Management Corporation.\n\n**Ownership of Parts of Land and Units**\n\n**92.** Unless otherwise specified in this Law, when a unit in a condominium building is sold, gifted, or mortgaged, the ownership of the unit shall be transferred to the purchaser, donee, or mortgagee in accordance with the procedures and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Registry of Units**\n\n**93.** The Ministry shall maintain a registry of condominium buildings for which strata plans have been approved, and any amendments made to strata plans under this Law.\n\n**Condominium Building Registry**\n\n**94.**\n(a) Upon approval of the strata plan, a registry of the condominium building comprising all units shall be prepared and maintained by the Council of the relevant city or island. A copy of this registry, certified as true to the original, shall be provided by the Council to the Management Corporation of the condominium building.\n(b) If the ownership of any unit included in the registry of a condominium building changes after the registration of the condominium building, that change shall be reflected in the condominium building registry in accordance with this Law and the regulations made thereunder.\n(c) If the ownership of any unit included in the registry of a condominium building changes, or if any amendments are made to the registry, that information shall be shared with the Management Corporation within 14 (fourteen) days of such change or amendment, in accordance with this Law and the regulations made thereunder.\n(d) Upon the creation of the condominium building registry in accordance with this Article, the land registry or the building and land registry pertaining to that building shall become void.\n\n**Registration of Units in Completed Buildings**\n\n**95.** Before issuing a unit registry for units within a condominium building, the following shall be ensured:\n(a) The authenticity of the documents submitted for registering the units;\n(b) That all fees payable to the government for the registration of units or for amendments to the unit registry under this Law and the regulations made thereunder have been paid;\n(c) If there are multiple owners for a unit within a condominium building, as described in subsection (b) of Article 85 of this Law, only one registry shall be issued for that unit;\n(d) That the requirements specified in the regulations made under this Law are met.\n\n**Registration of Units Under Stage Development**\n\n**96.** When applying for the registration of units within a condominium building under stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The form designated by the Ministry for applying for the registration of a unit within a condominium building under stage development;\n(b) Documentation from the original owner of the land for the sale of the unit within the condominium building;\n(c) A sales agreement or agreement registered with a court, notarized by a licensed notary public of the Maldives;\n(d) If the rental agreement is for the purchase of a unit, proof of full payment of the purchase price to the seller, or documentation of the payment plan;\n(e) If the land or unit of the condominium building is mortgaged, a document indicating the mortgagee\u0027s consent to the registration of the condominium building;\n(f) Other documents required to be submitted in accordance with the regulations governing stage development under this Law.\n\n**Issuance of Unit Registry for Completed Buildings**\n\n**97.** Strata plan approval shall be granted for completed buildings after ensuring the following:\n(a) That all common areas related to the units for which the strata plan approval is sought are completed and have been surveyed, and that the building conforms to the submitted strata plan;\n(b) That at least 2 (two) units of the building are completed, basic services are provided for those 2 (two) units, and a building use permit has been issued for the part of the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Registration of Units in Buildings with Completed Parts**\n\n**98.** When applying for strata plan approval for buildings where parts or units are completed, in addition to the documents specified in Article 52 of this Law, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The permit issued for the use of the completed part of the building;\n(b) Other information specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**99.** Approval of strata plans under stage development shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That the proposal submitted for carrying out the stage development project has been approved, and that an agreement for stage development has been signed between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(b) That all common areas related to the units for which strata plan approval is sought are completed, and that the building use permit has been issued for the parts of the building for which the strata plan approval is sought, conforming to the submitted strata plan;\n(c) That at least 20% (twenty percent) of the building for the stage development project has been completed, basic services are provided for those units, and a building use permit has been issued for the part of the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Application for Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**100.** When applying for strata plan approval under stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The application form for strata plan approval under stage development;\n(b) A document confirming the approval of the strata plan;\n(c) A progress report signed by the project manager or engineer, confirming that the project is proceeding in accordance with the stages outlined in the stage development agreement concluded between the parties;\n(d) The latest amended Schedule of Strata Units;\n(e) The building use permit issued for the completed part of the building.\n\n**Approval of Strata Plans Under Stage Development**\n\n**101.** Approval of strata plans under stage development shall be granted after ensuring the following:\n(a) That the proposal submitted for carrying out the stage development project has been approved, and that an agreement for stage development has been signed between the party developing the stage development and the Ministry;\n(b) That all common areas related to the units for which strata plan approval is sought are completed, and that the building use permit has been issued for the parts of the building for which the strata plan approval is sought, conforming to the submitted strata plan;\n(c) That at least 20% (twenty percent) of the building for the stage development project has been completed, basic services are provided for those units, and a building use permit has been issued for the part of the building for which strata plan approval is sought.\n\n**Chapter Five: Amendment of Strata Plans**\n\n**Application for Amendment of Strata Plans**\n\n**102.**\n(a) An application for amendment of a strata plan may be submitted to the Ministry by the original owner of the land or their designated representative, in accordance with the principles and standards set forth in this Law.\n(b) If an amendment is desired to a strata plan under a stage development, the amendment shall be made in accordance with the regulations governing stage development under this Law.\n(c) Amendments to strata plans for buildings constructed under government housing projects shall be made in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law concerning such projects.\n\n**Circumstances for Amending Share Units**\n\n**103.** The extent of the share allocated to units included in an approved strata plan may be amended under the following circumstances:\n(a) To amend the share unit allocated to a unit, to correct an error in the strata plan;\n(b) To amend the share unit due to a court order;\n(c) To make amendments to the building in accordance with the principles and standards for stage development provided in Chapter Seven of this Law;\n(d) To make amendments resulting from a redevelopment plan as specified in Article 47 of this Law.\n\n**Procedure for Amending Strata Plans**\n\n**104.** If an amendment is desired to a strata plan for which approval has been granted, the amendment can be made in accordance with the following procedures:\n(a) If any unit owner whose unit is affected by the proposed amendment to the strata plan has mortgaged their unit, the mortgage must consent to the amendment;\n(b) If the amendment is passed by a general resolution of the Management Corporation, provided that the resolution is passed with the votes of at least 80% (eighty percent) of the total share of all unit owners.\n\n**Documents Required for Amending Strata Plans**\n\n**105.** When applying for amendments to a strata plan, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The application form for amending the strata plan;\n(b) A copy of the latest approved and amended drawings;\n(c) A copy of the permit issued for the strata plan under this Law;\n(d) The amended strata plan, the amended Schedule of Strata Units, and the share schedule in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law;\n(e) A copy of the building use permit, if issued;\n(f) The general resolution of the Management Corporation approving the amendment to the strata plan, affixed with the corporation\u0027s seal;\n(g) If the amendment to the strata plan is made during the initial period, the documents required to be submitted for amending in accordance with the regulations governing stage development under this Law.\n\n**Amendment of Share Units**\n\n**106.** The extent of the share allocated to units included in an approved strata plan may be amended considering the following when amending the Schedule of Strata Units and the share extent allocated to units in accordance with Article 43 of this Law:\n(a) If a unit included in an approved strata plan has been sold, or if a registry has been issued for that unit, the share extent allocated to that unit may be amended only with the consent of the party who purchased the unit;\n(b) If a unit included in an approved strata plan under a stage development has not been sold, the share extent allocated to that unit may be amended without altering the total share extent of the building, after ensuring the latter.\n\n**Redevelopment of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**107.** If a condominium building is dilapidated or damaged due to an accident, or if the owners of the units in the condominium building wish to renovate the building, a redevelopment plan shall be prepared and submitted to the Ministry for approval in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Consolidation of Multiple Plots for Construction of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**108.** If the original owner(s) of the land wish to develop a condominium building by consolidating multiple registered plots of land, application for development shall only be made after consolidating all the plots into a single registry. Furthermore, upon such consolidation, the share of each owner corresponding to their respective units must be recorded in the registry.\n\n**Chapter Five: Management Corporation**\n\n**Management Corporation**\n\n**109.**\n(a) A Management Corporation is a legal entity with the capacity to sue and be sued in its own name, and shall possess its own seal.\n(b) A Management Corporation shall be registered for a building comprising at least 5 (five) units. Furthermore, for a building comprising 5 (five) units, the Management Corporation shall be registered only if at least 3 (three) of the unit owners are distinct parties.\n(c) For condominium buildings comprising fewer than 5 (five) units, the owners of the units shall establish a Management Agreement for the management and maintenance of those buildings and the fulfillment of the responsibilities of the Management Corporation as stipulated in this Law.\n(d) Upon the establishment of a Management Corporation, that corporation shall possess the capacities, powers, and responsibilities specified in this Chapter. The members of that corporation shall perform the powers and responsibilities vested in the corporation.\n\n**Objectives of the Management Corporation**\n\n**110.** The objectives of the Management Corporation are as follows:\n(a) To manage and maintain buildings registered as condominium buildings in the Maldives, in accordance with the strata scheme applicable to those buildings, as stipulated by this Law;\n(b) To manage and maintain the common areas and facilities within the buildings forming the strata scheme, carry out routine maintenance, and resolve emerging issues;\n(c) To establish fair principles among all unit owners to protect the interests of the owners of units within the strata scheme, and to carry out all necessary actions to uphold the rights of unit owners;\n(d) To convene meetings with the owners of all units, receive their opinions and address their concerns, find solutions to emerging issues, and foster good relations among unit owners.\n\n**Registration of Management Corporation**\n\n**111.**\n(a) Upon obtaining approval for the strata plan in accordance with Article 39 of this Law, the Management Corporation pertaining to that strata plan shall be registered with the Ministry in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n(b) The Ministry shall maintain a registry of Management Corporations registered under this Article.\n(c) Upon the registration of a Management Corporation in accordance with subsection (a) of this Article, the Ministry shall forward a copy of the approved strata plan and the Management Corporation\u0027s registration certificate to the Council within 15 (fifteen) days of the corporation\u0027s registration.\n(d) The principles and procedures for registering and operating Management Corporations shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Council of the Management Corporation**\n\n**112.**\n(a) The Council of the Management Corporation shall be elected by the members of the corporation through a vote to manage the affairs of the Management Corporation and to fulfill its responsibilities as outlined in this Law.\n(b) The number of members of the Council of the Management Corporation shall not be less than 3 (three).\n(c) Upon the registration of a Management Corporation, the first general meeting of the corporation shall elect the Chairman, Treasurer, and Secretary of the Council.\n\n**Members of the Management Corporation**\n\n**113.**\n(a) Upon the registration of a Management Corporation, the parties considered members of the Management Corporation shall be the Developer and the parties who purchase units in the condominium building under a sales agreement. Thus, the owner of each unit in the condominium building shall be a member of the Management Corporation.\n(b) As units in the condominium building are sold by the Developer after the registration of the Management Corporation, the number of members of the corporation shall increase accordingly. Each such party shall be considered a member of the corporation from the moment they sign the sales agreement for the purchase of a unit.\n(c) If a party who has purchased a unit under a sales agreement becomes a member of the Management Corporation from the date of signing the agreement, that party shall cease to be a member of the corporation upon the termination of that agreement.\n(d) The Developer shall remain a member of the Management Corporation until the end of the defect liability period applicable to the building.\n\n**Relationship Between Developer and Management Corporation**\n\n**114.**\n(a) During the initial period, the Developer shall manage and maintain the Management Corporation and all matters related to the strata scheme, common areas, and facilities within the condominium building.\n(b) Upon the expiry of the initial period, the Developer shall fulfill the responsibilities assumed by the Developer under subsection (a) of this Article, in accordance with the directives passed by the Management Corporation as a member thereof, or according to the Corporation\u0027s decisions.\n(c) In situations where the powers and responsibilities of the Developer pertaining to the units and common areas of the condominium building are consistent with the powers and responsibilities of the Management Corporation, and in the absence of another party appointed by the Management Corporation, the Developer shall act as the Managing Agent.\n\n**Handover of Documents to the Management Corporation**\n\n**115.** Upon the establishment of the Management Corporation, the original owner of the land or the Developer shall hand over the following documents to the Corporation:\n(a) Copies of all approved building drawings and all permits related to construction;\n(b) A copy of the permit issued for the strata plan;\n(c) Copies of the building use permit and permits issued for residential/commercial use;\n(d) Information and drawings related to common areas;\n(e) Copies of fire safety certificates;\n(f) Schedule for building maintenance and cleaning;\n(g) Details of the building\u0027s insurance policy and depreciation schedule;\n(h) Other documents specified in the regulations made under this Law, in addition to the documents mentioned in subsections (a) to (g) of this Article.\n\n**Responsibilities of the Management Corporation**\n\n**116.** The responsibilities of the Management Corporation include, in accordance with this Law, the regulations made thereunder, and the decisions of the Corporation:\n(a) To maintain the common areas of the condominium building at a consistent standard;\n(b) To carry out necessary repairs and maintenance of common areas and facilities to maintain a consistent standard;\n(c) To collect the fees payable by the owners of the units;\n(d) To maintain insurance for the building at its replacement value, including obtaining a contractor\u0027s all-risk insurance policy for the construction period, and to pay insurance premiums;\n(e) To obtain a performance guarantee and a bank guarantee or insurance bond for the sale of units within the scope of the stage development;\n(f) To fulfill all obligations required of the Developer during the initial period and at various stages of the stage development;\n(g) To make amendments to the strata plan in accordance with this Law and the regulations made thereunder, and to obtain approval for the strata scheme and to finalize the scheme;\n(h) To maintain all records related to the stage development;\n(i) To fulfill all responsibilities required of the Developer during the various stages of the stage development, in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law, upon the formation of the Management Corporation.\n\n**Meetings of the Management Corporation**\n\n**117.**\n(a) An annual general meeting of the Management Corporation shall be held at least once every calendar year.\n(b) The procedures for holding the first general meeting, annual general meetings, general meetings, and extraordinary meetings of the Management Corporation, the conduct of such meetings, and the decision-making process of the Management Corporation shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Voting**\n\n**118.**\n(a) Each member of the Management Corporation shall have the right to attend and vote at the corporation\u0027s meetings.\n(b) In matters relating to the strata scheme, each member shall have voting rights corresponding to the extent of their share in the unit.\n(c) The procedures for voting at meetings of the Management Corporation shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Obligations of Unit Owners to the Management Corporation**\n\n**119.** Unit owners shall fulfill the following obligations to the Management Corporation in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law and the regulations made thereunder:\n(a) To fully comply with the decisions and directives issued by the Management Corporation;\n(b) To pay the maintenance fees determined by the Management Corporation in accordance with the principles and standards for the management and use of the condominium building.\n\n**Procedure for Non-Payment of Maintenance Fees**\n\n**120.** If any unit owner fails to pay the maintenance fees as determined by this Law and the regulations made thereunder, the Management Corporation shall take action against such parties based on a resolution passed by a majority of the members present and voting at a general meeting of the Management Corporation, in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Appointment of Managing Agent**\n\n**121.**\n(a) The Management Corporation may appoint a Managing Agent to carry out repairs and maintenance of the common areas of the strata scheme as needed, according to the following procedures:\n(1) Appointment of a Managing Agent after passing a resolution at a general meeting of the Management Corporation;\n(2) The appointed Managing Agent must be a company, partnership, or cooperative society registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership.\n(b) The procedures for appointing a Managing Agent and the responsibilities of the Managing Agent shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Principles for Management and Use of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**122.** The principles for the management, maintenance, and use of condominium buildings shall be prepared by the Management Corporation, passed at a meeting of the Corporation, and publicly disclosed, in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law and the regulations made thereunder.\n\n**Information to be Included in the Strata Roll**\n\n**123.** The Management Corporation shall prepare and maintain the strata roll, which shall include the following information:\n(a) The strata plan number;\n(b) The number of units within the condominium building and the extent of the share allocated to each unit;\n(c) The names of the owners of the units within the condominium building;\n(d) Information about the Managing Agent, if appointed for the management of the condominium building;\n(e) Information regarding the insurance of the condominium building;\n(f) The regulations and principles formulated for the scheme;\n(g) Details of any mortgages on the condominium building;\n(h) Information about the landlords.\n\n**Chapter Eight: Registration of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**Registration of Condominium Building Units**\n\n**124.** Upon approval of the strata plan, the owner of each unit in the condominium building shall apply for the registration of their unit in their name, in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law and the regulations made thereunder, to the Council of the relevant city or island.\n(a) Applications for the registration of units in a condominium building for which a strata plan has been approved shall be submitted to the Ministry using the form designated by the Ministry.\n(b) The circumstances under which application may be made for the registration of condominium building units are as follows:\n(1) For the initial registration of units within a condominium building;\n(2) To amend the unit registry due to any change in an approved strata plan;\n(3) To amend the unit registry due to the sale of a registered unit of a condominium building.\n\n**Application for Registration of Units Under Stage Development**\n\n**125.** When applying for the registration of units within a condominium building under stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The form designated by the Ministry for applying for the purchase and sale of a unit within a condominium building under stage development;\n(b) Documentation from the original owner of the land for the sale of the unit within the condominium building;\n(c) A sales agreement notarized by a licensed notary public of the Maldives Bar Council, or an agreement registered with a court;\n(d) If the agreement mentioned in subsection (c) of this Article requires payment of the unit price, proof of full payment of the unit price to the seller;\n(e) If the land or unit of the condominium building is mortgaged, a document indicating the mortgagee\u0027s consent to the registration of the condominium building;\n(f) Other documents required to be submitted in accordance with the principles and standards for stage development as specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Transfer of Unit Registry to Another Party**\n\n**126.**\n(a) The rights of the owner of a unit in a condominium building, including the right to inherit or gift units, may be transferred to another party with the written consent of the landlord.\n(b) Upon the transfer of the owner\u0027s rights in a unit of a condominium building due to sale, gift, devise, or inheritance, all rights of the original owner of the unit shall transfer to the new owner, and the unit registry shall be amended accordingly.\n(c) If the owner of a unit in a condominium building wishes to transfer their rights in the unit to a third party upon application to the landlord, the landlord shall not unreasonably withhold such permission.\n(d) If the owner of a unit in a condominium building applies to the landlord for permission to transfer their rights to a third party, the landlord shall not charge any additional fee from the tenant for granting such permission.\n\n**Registration of Units in Completed Buildings**\n\n**127.** The registration of units in condominium buildings shall be carried out in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n(a) Upon approval of the strata plan, the owner of each unit in the condominium building shall apply for the registration of their unit in their name, in accordance with the principles and standards set forth in this Law and the regulations made thereunder, to the Council of the respective city or island.\n(b) The circumstances under which application may be made for the registration of condominium building units are as follows:\n(1) For the initial registration of units within a condominium building;\n(2) To amend the unit registry due to any change in an approved strata plan;\n(3) To amend the unit registry due to the sale of a registered unit of a condominium building.\n\n**Application for Unit Registration Under Stage Development**\n\n**128.** When applying for the registration of units within a condominium building under stage development, the following documents must be submitted:\n(a) The form designated by the Ministry for applying for the purchase and sale of a unit within a condominium building under stage development;\n(b) Documentation from the original owner of the land for the sale of the unit within the condominium building;\n(c) A sales agreement or agreement registered with a court, notarized by a licensed notary public of the Maldives Bar Council;\n(d) If the rental agreement requires payment of the unit price, proof of full payment of the purchase price to the seller;\n(e) If the land or unit of the condominium building is mortgaged, a document indicating the mortgagee\u0027s consent to the registration of the condominium building;\n(f) Other documents required to be submitted in accordance with the principles and standards for stage development as specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Transfer of Unit Registry to Another Party**\n\n**129.**\n(a) The rights of the owner of a unit in a condominium building, including the right to inherit or gift units, may be transferred to another party with the written consent of the landlord.\n(b) Upon the transfer of the owner\u0027s rights in a unit of a condominium building due to sale, gift, devise, or inheritance, all rights of the original owner of the unit shall transfer to the new owner, and the unit registry shall be amended accordingly.\n(c) The ownership of common areas in a condominium building by the owner of a unit is a right shared equally with the owners of other units, and it is inseparable from that unit. Therefore, any transaction such as sale, gift, devise, or mortgage of common areas shall be conducted in a manner that does not prejudice the rights of other unit owners and in accordance with the strata scheme.\n(d) When a unit owner of a condominium building sells, gifts, devises, or mortgages their unit, the unit purchaser, donee, or legatee shall acquire ownership of the unit in proportion to their share of the common areas, in accordance with the strata plan.\n\n**Ownership of Land and Units in Buildings**\n\n**130.**\n(a) Unless otherwise specified in this Law, upon the registration of a condominium building, the owner of each unit in the building shall be considered the owner of the land in proportion to the share allocated to that unit in the strata plan and schedule of strata units.\n(b) The purchase, sale, gift, devise, or mortgage of units within a condominium building shall be restricted to Maldivian citizens, companies, partnerships, cooperative societies, or associations registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership.\n(c) Companies, partnerships, or cooperative societies registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership that have purchased units in a condominium building shall not sell any share of their ownership to foreign parties.\n(d) When selling a unit in a condominium building, the owner of the unit must ensure that the purchaser agrees to abide by the responsibilities and obligations of the Management Corporation and to comply with the decisions and regulations of the Management Corporation.\n\n**Ownership of Parts of Land and Units**\n\n**131.**\n(a) Unless otherwise specified in this Law, upon the registration of a condominium building, the owner of each unit in the building shall be considered the owner of the land in proportion to the share allocated to that unit in the strata plan and schedule of strata units.\n(b) The purchase, sale, gift, devise, or mortgage of units within a condominium building shall be restricted to Maldivian citizens, companies, partnerships, cooperative societies, or associations registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership.\n(c) Companies, partnerships, or cooperative societies registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership that have purchased units in a condominium building shall not sell any share of their ownership to foreign parties.\n(d) When selling a unit in a condominium building, the owner of the unit must ensure that the purchaser agrees to abide by the responsibilities and obligations of the Management Corporation and to comply with the decisions and regulations of the Management Corporation.\n\n**Ownership of Land in Government Housing Projects**\n\n**132.** Unless otherwise specified in any other law, ownership of land or plots pertaining to buildings constructed under government social housing projects shall be granted to the recipients or purchasers of housing units in accordance with government policy.\n\n**Regulations on Unit Registration**\n\n**133.** The procedures for applying for the registration of units within a condominium building and for carrying out transactions related to the unit registry shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Chapter Nine: Transactions Related to the Sale, Disposal, and Registration of Condominium Building Units**\n\n**Transactions Related to the Unit Registry**\n\n**134.** All transactions related to the unit registry of a condominium building shall be carried out in accordance with the principles and standards set forth in this Chapter.\n\n**Transactions Related to Condominium Building Units**\n\n**135.**\n(a) The owner of a unit in a condominium building has the full right to rent, sell, gift, devise, or mortgage that unit, in accordance with the provisions of this Law and the regulations made thereunder.\n(b) As a condominium building possesses a distinct legal status, the registration of a condominium building and the transactions related to units within the building, common areas, and the strata scheme, shall not be separated from the land, unless otherwise specified in another article of this Law.\n(c) It is prohibited to sell, gift, devise, or mortgage any part of the common areas of a condominium building, or to rent them out, separately from the unit to which they relate.\n(d) It is prohibited to use any unit in a condominium building for purposes contrary to its designated use, whether through renting, selling, gifting, devising, or mortgaging.\n\n**Ownership of Land and Units in Buildings**\n\n**136.**\n(a) Unless otherwise specified in this Law, the owner of each unit in a condominium building constructed on government or private land shall be considered the owner of the land in proportion to the share allocated to that unit in the strata plan and schedule of strata units.\n(b) The purchase, sale, gift, devise, or mortgage of units within a condominium building shall be restricted to Maldivian citizens, companies, partnerships, cooperative societies, or associations registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership.\n(c) Companies, partnerships, or cooperative societies registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership that have purchased units in a condominium building shall not sell any share of their ownership to foreign parties.\n(d) When selling a unit in a condominium building, the owner of the unit must ensure that the purchaser agrees to abide by the responsibilities and obligations of the Management Corporation and to comply with the decisions and regulations of the Management Corporation.\n\n**Ownership of Parts of Land and Units**\n\n**137.**\n(a) Unless otherwise specified in this Law, upon the registration of a condominium building, the owner of each unit in the building shall be considered the owner of the land in proportion to the share allocated to that unit in the strata plan and schedule of strata units.\n(b) The purchase, sale, gift, devise, or mortgage of units within a condominium building shall be restricted to Maldivian citizens, companies, partnerships, cooperative societies, or associations registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership.\n(c) Companies, partnerships, or cooperative societies registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership that have purchased units in a condominium building shall not sell any share of their ownership to foreign parties.\n(d) When selling a unit in a condominium building, the owner of the unit must ensure that the purchaser agrees to abide by the responsibilities and obligations of the Management Corporation and to comply with the decisions and regulations of the Management Corporation.\n\n**Separation of Ownership of Parts of Buildings**\n\n**138.**\n(a) Unless otherwise specified in this Law, if a unit within a condominium building is sold, gifted, or devised, the owner of that unit shall also be considered the owner of the land in proportion to the share allocated to that unit. Furthermore, the ownership of common areas within the condominium building shall be shared equally among all unit owners.\n(b) If a unit in a condominium building is sold, gifted, or devised, the ownership of the unit shall be transferred to the purchaser, donee, or legatee, and the unit registry shall be amended accordingly.\n(c) The ownership of common areas in a condominium building by the owner of a unit is a right shared equally with the owners of other units, and it is inseparable from that unit. Therefore, any transaction such as sale, gift, devise, or mortgage of common areas shall be conducted in a manner that does not prejudice the rights of other unit owners and in accordance with the strata scheme.\n(d) When a unit owner of a condominium building sells, gifts, devises, or mortgages their unit, the unit purchaser, donee, or legatee shall acquire ownership of the unit in proportion to their share of the common areas, in accordance with the strata plan.\n\n**Individualization of Units in Condominium Buildings on Government Land**\n\n**139.**\n(a) When a unit or units within a condominium building constructed on government land are to be individually registered, and if the original owner of the land wishes to individually register the units, the ownership of the land pertaining to that building shall be determined according to government policy.\n(b) If the original owner of the land wishes to individually register units within a condominium building constructed on government land, and if the land is government property, the share of the land allocated to each unit cannot be individually registered. However, if the owners of the units wish to individually register units within a condominium building constructed on government land, the land may be privatized after paying the fee determined by the Land Act and its regulations. Upon such privatization, the building shall be considered a building on privately owned land.\n(c) All decisions regarding the privatization of land for condominium buildings as described in subsection (b) of this Article must be made with the approval of all unit owners through the Management Corporation.\n\n**Regulations on Unit Registration**\n\n**140.** The procedures for applying for the registration of units within a condominium building and for carrying out transactions related to the unit registry shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Chapter Ten: Management Corporation**\n\n**Management Corporation**\n\n**141.**\n(a) A Management Corporation is a legal entity with the capacity to sue and be sued in its own name, and shall possess its own seal.\n(b) A Management Corporation shall be registered for a building comprising at least 5 (five) units. Furthermore, for a building comprising 5 (five) units, the Management Corporation shall be registered only if at least 3 (three) of the unit owners are distinct parties.\n(c) For condominium buildings comprising fewer than 5 (five) units, the owners of the units shall establish a Management Agreement for the management and maintenance of those buildings and the fulfillment of the responsibilities of the Management Corporation as stipulated in this Law.\n(d) Upon the establishment of a Management Corporation, that corporation shall possess the capacities, powers, and responsibilities specified in this Chapter. The members of that corporation shall perform the powers and responsibilities vested in the corporation.\n\n**Objectives of the Management Corporation**\n\n**142.** The objectives of the Management Corporation are as follows:\n(a) To manage and maintain buildings registered as condominium buildings in the Maldives, in accordance with the strata scheme applicable to those buildings, as stipulated by this Law;\n(b) To manage and maintain the common areas and facilities within the buildings forming the strata scheme, carry out routine maintenance, and resolve emerging issues;\n(c) To establish fair principles among all unit owners to protect the interests of the owners of units within the strata scheme, and to carry out all necessary actions to uphold the rights of unit owners;\n(d) To convene meetings with the owners of all units, receive their opinions and address their concerns, find solutions to emerging issues, and foster good relations among unit owners.\n\n**Registration of Management Corporation**\n\n**143.**\n(a) Upon obtaining approval for the strata plan in accordance with Article 39 of this Law, the Management Corporation pertaining to that strata plan shall be registered with the Ministry in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n(b) The Ministry shall maintain a registry of Management Corporations registered under this Article.\n(c) Upon the registration of a Management Corporation in accordance with subsection (a) of this Article, the Ministry shall forward a copy of the approved strata plan and the Management Corporation\u0027s registration certificate to the Council within 15 (fifteen) days of the corporation\u0027s registration.\n(d) The principles and procedures for registering and operating Management Corporations shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Council of the Management Corporation**\n\n**144.**\n(a) The Council of the Management Corporation shall be elected by the members of the corporation through a vote to manage the affairs of the Management Corporation and to fulfill its responsibilities as outlined in this Law.\n(b) The number of members of the Council of the Management Corporation shall not be less than 3 (three).\n(c) Upon the registration of a Management Corporation, the first general meeting of the corporation shall elect the Chairman, Treasurer, and Secretary of the Council.\n\n**Members of the Management Corporation**\n\n**145.**\n(a) Upon the registration of a Management Corporation, the parties considered members of the Management Corporation shall be the Developer and the parties who purchase units in the condominium building under a sales agreement. Thus, the owner of each unit in the condominium building shall be a member of the Management Corporation.\n(b) As units in the condominium building are sold by the Developer after the registration of the Management Corporation, the number of members of the corporation shall increase accordingly. Each such party shall be considered a member of the corporation from the moment they sign the sales agreement for the purchase of a unit.\n(c) If a party who has purchased a unit under a sales agreement becomes a member of the Management Corporation from the date of signing the agreement, that party shall cease to be a member of the corporation upon the termination of that agreement.\n(d) The Developer shall remain a member of the Management Corporation until the end of the defect liability period applicable to the building.\n\n**Relationship Between Developer and Management Corporation**\n\n**146.**\n(a) During the initial period, the Developer shall manage and maintain the Management Corporation and all matters related to the strata scheme, common areas, and facilities within the condominium building.\n(b) Upon the expiry of the initial period, the Developer shall fulfill the responsibilities assumed by the Developer under subsection (a) of this Article, in accordance with the directives passed by the Management Corporation as a member thereof, or according to the Corporation\u0027s decisions.\n(c) In situations where the powers and responsibilities of the Developer pertaining to the units and common areas of the condominium building are consistent with the powers and responsibilities of the Management Corporation, and in the absence of another party appointed by the Management Corporation, the Developer shall act as the Managing Agent.\n\n**Handover of Documents to the Management Corporation**\n\n**147.** Upon the establishment of the Management Corporation, the original owner of the land or the Developer shall hand over the following documents to the Corporation:\n(a) Copies of all approved building drawings and all permits related to construction;\n(b) A copy of the permit issued for the strata plan;\n(c) Copies of the building use permit and permits issued for residential/commercial use;\n(d) Information and drawings related to common areas;\n(e) Copies of fire safety certificates;\n(f) Schedule for building maintenance and cleaning;\n(g) Details of the building\u0027s insurance policy and depreciation schedule;\n(h) Other documents specified in the regulations made under this Law, in addition to the documents mentioned in subsections (a) to (g) of this Article.\n\n**Responsibilities of the Management Corporation**\n\n**148.** The responsibilities of the Management Corporation include, in accordance with this Law, the regulations made thereunder, and the decisions of the Corporation:\n(a) To maintain the common areas of the condominium building at a consistent standard;\n(b) To carry out necessary repairs and maintenance of common areas and facilities to maintain a consistent standard;\n(c) To collect the fees payable by the owners of the units;\n(d) To maintain insurance for the building at its replacement value, including obtaining a contractor\u0027s all-risk insurance policy for the construction period, and to pay insurance premiums;\n(e) To provide notices and directives from government authorities related to building use and maintenance to the unit owners;\n(f) To implement the decisions of the Management Corporation;\n(g) To maintain financial statements of the Management Corporation and to have them audited regularly and submitted to the relevant authorities;\n(h) To hold a general meeting at least once every year;\n(i) To carry out all necessary work for the operation of the Management Corporation;\n(j) To perform other functions as specified in this Law and the regulations made thereunder.\n\n**Meetings of the Management Corporation**\n\n**149.**\n(a) An annual general meeting of the Management Corporation shall be held at least once every calendar year.\n(b) The procedures for holding the first general meeting, annual general meetings, general meetings, and extraordinary meetings of the Management Corporation, the conduct of such meetings, and the decision-making process of the Management Corporation shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Voting**\n\n**150.**\n(a) Each member of the Management Corporation shall have the right to attend and vote at the corporation\u0027s meetings.\n(b) In matters relating to the strata scheme, each member shall have voting rights corresponding to the extent of their share in the unit.\n(c) The procedures for voting at meetings of the Management Corporation shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Obligations of Unit Owners to the Management Corporation**\n\n**151.** Unit owners shall fulfill the following obligations to the Management Corporation in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law and the regulations made thereunder:\n(a) To fully comply with the decisions and directives issued by the Management Corporation;\n(b) To pay the maintenance fees determined by the Management Corporation in accordance with the principles and standards for the management and use of the condominium building.\n\n**Procedure for Non-Payment of Maintenance Fees**\n\n**152.** If any unit owner fails to pay the maintenance fees as determined by this Law and the regulations made thereunder, the Management Corporation shall take action against such parties based on a resolution passed by a majority of the members present and voting at a general meeting of the Management Corporation, in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Appointment of Managing Agent**\n\n**153.**\n(a) The Management Corporation may appoint a Managing Agent to carry out repairs and maintenance of the common areas of the strata scheme as needed, according to the following procedures:\n(1) Appointment of a Managing Agent after passing a resolution at a general meeting of the Management Corporation;\n(2) The appointed Managing Agent must be a company, partnership, or cooperative society registered in the Maldives with 100% (one hundred percent) Maldivian ownership.\n(b) The procedures for appointing a Managing Agent and the responsibilities of the Managing Agent shall be specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Principles for Management and Use of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**154.** The principles for the management, maintenance, and use of condominium buildings shall be prepared by the Management Corporation, passed at a meeting of the Corporation, and publicly disclosed, in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law and the regulations made thereunder.\n\n**Information to be Included in the Strata Roll**\n\n**155.** The Management Corporation shall prepare and maintain the strata roll, which shall include the following information:\n(a) The strata plan number;\n(b) The number of units within the condominium building and the extent of the share allocated to each unit;\n(c) The names of the owners of the units within the condominium building;\n(d) Information about the Managing Agent, if appointed for the management of the condominium building;\n(e) Information regarding the insurance of the condominium building;\n(f) The regulations and principles formulated for the scheme;\n(g) Details of any mortgages on the condominium building.\n\n**Chapter Eleven: Funds**\n\n**Establishment of Funds**\n\n**156.**\n(a) The Management Corporation shall establish and maintain a Maintenance Fund to cover the recurring expenses associated with the use and maintenance of the condominium building or buildings.\n(b) In addition to the Maintenance Fund described in subsection (a) of this Article, the Management Corporation may establish funds to cover capital expenses related to the use and maintenance of the condominium building or buildings, or to prepare for unforeseen circumstances, to meet all obligations related to the formation of the Management Corporation under this Law.\n\n**Period for Opening Maintenance Fund**\n\n**157.** The Maintenance Fund shall be opened within the following periods:\n(a) Within 30 (thirty) days from the date of obtaining the temporary building use permit for a unit in a condominium building;\n(b) For a building registered as a condominium building before the commencement of this Law, the Management Corporation pertaining to that building shall be registered within 30 (thirty) days from the commencement date of this Law.\n\n**Use of Maintenance Fund**\n\n**158.** The Maintenance Fund shall be used for the following purposes:\n(a) To cover expenses for the repair and maintenance of the building, cleaning of common areas, and security services;\n(b) To pay insurance premiums;\n(c) To cover fees for auditing the financial statements of the Management Corporation;\n(d) To cover expenses for managing the Maintenance Fund and administrative costs.\n\n**Developer\u0027s Obligations Relating to the Maintenance Fund**\n\n**159.**\n(a) The Developer\u0027s obligations relating to the Maintenance Fund include the following:\n(1) To pay the applicable maintenance fees for each unit from the date of obtaining the building use permit for that unit, to the Fund;\n(2) If the fee referred to in sub-point (1) of this paragraph is collected from the unit owner under a sales agreement, to pay such fees to the Maintenance Fund after collecting them;\n(3) If a unit in the condominium building has not been sold, and if a building use permit has been obtained for that unit, to pay the monthly maintenance fees allocated to that unit regularly until the unit is sold;\n(4) If a unit in the condominium building has been sold, and if a building use permit has not been obtained for that unit, to pay the monthly maintenance fees allocated to that unit regularly until the building use permit is obtained;\n(5) Upon the establishment of the Maintenance Fund for the condominium building, to deposit any income generated from the use of common areas into the Maintenance Fund;\n(6) To deposit fees collected for limited common property under the regulations made under this Law into the Maintenance Fund.\n(b) If the Developer does not obtain the completion certificate for a project under stage development, the developer may collect maintenance fees from the purchasers of units in that project only with the approval of the Ministry.\n\n**Opening of Project Account**\n\n**160.** Parties developing and managing condominium buildings under stage development shall open a Project Account in a bank licensed by the Maldives Monetary Authority to conduct all financial transactions related to the project, in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law and the regulations made thereunder.\n\n**Financial Transactions Related to Projects**\n\n**161.** Funds shall be deposited into and disbursed from the Project Account in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law and the regulations made thereunder. Furthermore, the regulations made under this Law shall specify the procedures for financial transactions related to the project by the Developer and the measures to be taken against parties violating this Law and those regulations.\n(c) To maintain the financial statements of the Management Corporation and to have them audited regularly and submitted to the relevant authorities.\n\n**Chapter Twelve: Rights of Owners**\n\n**Right to Use Common Areas of Condominium Buildings**\n\n**115.**\n(a) The owner of a unit in a condominium building is entitled to all rights pertaining to that unit.\n(b) In addition to the rights mentioned in subsection (a) of this Article, the owner of a unit in a condominium building also has the right to use the common areas together with the owners of other units.\n\n**Facilities Related to Services**\n\n**116.** The owners of units and the Management Corporation have the right to establish, maintain, and repair facilities related to services required for the units in a condominium building, in accordance with the principles and standards specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n\n**Right to Security from Building Parts for Unit**\n\n**117.**\n(a) The owner of each unit is entitled to security from all parts of the building pertaining to that unit.\n(b) For the purposes of subsection (a) of this Article, all parts of the building that provide security to the unit include the external walls of the building, the structure of the building, the roof, and the boundary walls between the unit and other units.\n(c) The right of the owner of a unit to security from the parts of the building shall be proportional to the rights enjoyed by the owners of other units. Similarly, the right to use the common areas of the condominium building shall be proportional to the rights enjoyed by the owners of other units.\n\n**Inseparability of Interests**\n\n**118.** The rights and interests of a unit owner pertaining to their unit are inseparable from the rights and interests they have concerning the common areas of the condominium building.\n\n**Chapter Thirteen: Responsibilities of Councils**\n\n**Responsibilities of Councils**\n\n**119.** Unless otherwise specified in this Law, the responsibilities of the Councils are as follows:\n(a) To verify and ensure that the drawings submitted for the registration of a condominium building conform to the standards and regulations for construction stipulated by the relevant laws and planning standards of the Maldives;\n(b) To issue condominium building registries and unit registries in accordance with the principles and standards specified in this Law and the regulations made thereunder;\n(c) To verify and ensure that any changes made to the strata plan of a building for which a strata plan has been approved are in accordance with the planning standards and regulations of the Maldives;\n(d) To issue building use permits for buildings subject to strata plans;\n(e) To provide advice and guidance to the Minister, when required, on matters arising in connection with the management and use of registered condominium buildings, after the registration of those buildings;\n(f) To prohibit the issuance of permits for uses other than those designated for buildings subject to strata plans, and to take necessary actions in cases of permit refusal.\n\n**Application for Permits to Councils**\n\n**120.** Applications for permits related to the responsibilities of the Councils as outlined in this Chapter shall be submitted to the Council of the island or city where the building is located.\n\n**Issuance of Permits by Councils**\n\n**121.**\n(a) Upon submission of drawings for the approval of a condominium building, the Council shall verify that the parts of the building are designated for use in accordance with the provisions of Chapter Three of this Law.\n(b) If the drawings submitted for approval conform to the conditions specified in Chapter Three of this Law, and if the land and building are divided into parts in accordance with the planning regulations, the Council shall approve the drawings.\n(c) If an application is submitted to amend the drawings for which strata plan approval has been granted, the amendment shall be approved by the Council in accordance with the procedures specified in the regulations made under this Law.\n(d) If approval has been granted for a strata plan for 2 (two) consolidated plots of land under a redevelopment plan, in accordance with Article 47 of this Law, the necessary actions related to the amendments to those buildings shall be carried out under the guidance and advice of the Ministry.\n(e) If a strata plan for which approval has been granted needs to be cancelled, this shall be done under the guidance and advice of the Ministry.\n(f) If the conditions specified in the regulations made under this Law are met for an application submitted to the Council for a permit related to any matter under this Law, the Council shall issue the permit within 45 (forty-five) days from the date of submission.\n(g) If the Council determines that the requirements specified in the regulations made under this Law are not met for an application submitted for a permit related to any matter under this Law, the Council shall inform the applicant of this determination within 10 (ten) days and return all submitted documents to the applicant.\n\n**Sharing of Information from Condominium Building Registry**\n\n**122.** If the ownership of any unit in a condominium building changes, or if any amendments are made to the registry, that information shall be reported to the Ministry within a maximum of 14 (fourteen) days.\n\n**Chapter Ten: General Provisions**\n\n**Condominium Buildings Registered Under the Land Act**\n\n**123.** Upon the commencement of this Law, buildings registered as condominium buildings under the Land Act shall be subject to the system established by this Law. Furthermore, the owners of the units in such buildings shall fulfill all obligations required under this Law within 12 (twelve) months from the commencement date of this Law.\n\n**Repeal of Articles and Regulations**\n\n**124.** Upon the commencement of this Law, the following articles of law and regulations shall be repealed:\n(a) Article 28 of the Land Act (Law No. 1/2002).\n(b) All articles pertaining to residential rentals in the \"Regulations on Renting Land and Buildings Constructed on Land\".\n\n**Non-Consideration of Compliance with Other Laws**\n\n**125.** The registration of a condominium building under this Law shall not be considered evidence of compliance with requirements mandated by any other law or regulation related to construction. Furthermore, the owner of the land shall be obligated to fulfill all requirements mandated by any law or regulation related to construction in relation to that building.\n\n**Making of Regulations**\n\n**126.**\n(a) Unless otherwise specified in this Law, the Ministry shall make and enforce all regulations required under this Law.\n(b) Unless otherwise specified in this Law, all regulations required to be made under this Law shall be made and published in the Government Gazette of the Maldives within 4 (four) months from the commencement date of this Law.\n\n**Commencement of the Law**\n\n**127.** This Law shall come into effect from the date on which 3 (three) months have passed from the date it is passed, ratified, and published in the Government Gazette of the Maldives.\n\n**Interpretation**\n\n**128.** Unless the context otherwise requires, the following terms and phrases used in this Law shall have the meanings assigned to them below:\n(a) \"Ministry\" refers to the government ministry responsible for matters related to condominium buildings.\n(b) \"Council\" refers to the City Councils and Island Councils established under Law No. 7/2010 (Decentralization Act of the Maldives).\n(c) \"Minister\" refers to the Minister of the government ministry responsible for matters related to condominium buildings.\n(d) \"Basic Services\" refers to the water, electricity, and sewerage services required for the occupancy of a building.\n(e) \"Commercial Purpose\" refers to commercial activities conducted in accordance with Law No. 18/2014 (Business Registration Act).\n(f) \"Land Act\" refers to Law No. 1/2002 (Maldives Land Act) and any amendments thereto.\n(g) \"Law on Construction\" refers to Law No. 4/2017 (Law on Construction) and any amendments thereto.\n\n**Law No.: 33/2021**\n**Effective from: 20 March 2022**\n\n**Copyright © 2023 Attorney General\u0027s Office**",
